        <h1>Password Strength Checker API</h1>

        <p>Hello and welcome to the Password Strength Checker API.</p>
        <p>This API helps you check the strength of a password, and also checks if it has been found in any data breaches.</p>
        <hr>
        <h2>How to Use:</h2>
        <p>Make a POST request to the following endpoint:</p>
        <pre><code>POST /check</code></pre>

        <p>The request body should contain a <code>password</code> field, as the <b>key&value</b> pair shown below:</p>

        <pre><code>{ 
    "password": "yourPassword123!" 
 }</code></pre>
        <hr>
        <h2>Response:</h2>
        <p>The API will respond with a <code>result</code> (JSON object) containing the password strength analysis. If the password has been found in breached databases, the API will indicate that as well.</p>

        <p>Example response:</p>

        <pre><code>{ 
    "result": "Password found in several breached databases" 
 }</code></pre>

        <p>If the password was not found in any known breached database, you may receive one of the following responses:</p>

        <ul>
            <li>"Password is too short"</li>
            <li>"Password contains space"</li>
            <li>"Excellent strength"</li>
            <li>"Good strength"</li>
            <li>"Poor strength"</li>
        </ul>
        <hr>
        <h2>Sample cURL Request:</h2>
    <pre><code>curl -X POST https://password-strength-checker-au80.onrender.com/check/ \
-H "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded" \
--data-urlencode "password=yourPasswordHere"</code></pre>

    <h2>Response:</h2>
    <p>Returns a JSON object containing a <code>result</code> field describing the password strength or warning.</p>
    <hr>

    <h2>How Passwords Are Evaluated:</h2>
    <p>The API evaluates the password based on the following criteria:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Empty Password:</strong> No password field provided in the request.</li>
        <li><strong>Breached Password:</strong> Password appears in a known data breach.</li>
        <li><strong>Whitespace Check:</strong> Password contains spaces, which is not allowed.</li>
        <li><strong>Length Check:</strong> Password must be at least 8 characters long.</li>
        <li><strong>Character Composition:</strong></li>
        <ol>
            <li><strong>Excellent strength:</strong> Contains letters, numbers, and special characters.</li>
            <li><strong>Good strength:</strong> Contains any two of the three: letters, numbers, or special characters.</li>
            <li><strong>Poor strength:</strong> Contains only one of the three: letters, numbers, or special characters.</li>
        </ol>
    </ul>
    <hr>
    <h2>Important Notes:</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The password is hashed and checked against known data breaches using the "Pwned Passwords" service.</li>
            <li>If not found, the API checks for password strength based on length, use of letters, numbers, special characters, and spaces.</li>
        </ul>
